Description:
Patrick Morin
Well established in the hearts of Quebecers for over 60 years, Patrick Morin has carved out an imposing place for itself in the hardware industry in several regions of Quebec. With 21 branches and more than 1,700 employees, the company quickly became an important pillar of the industry, building an unparalleled reputation for itself. Newly acquired by experienced people since February 2021, we can now add to our already winning philosophy, the essential element to the vision of expansion and challenges conveyed by our new leaders, namely their employees’ happiness. By being part of the team, you make sure you join a company that will develop the immensity of your potential, regardless of your role.
We offer:
A pleasant working environment
: One of our strengths is undoubtedly fun at work and team spirit! We make up our team of enthusiastic, dedicated, proud people who prioritize collective goals over individual ones.
The pride of working in a well-established Quebec company that has the wind in its sails!
And much more:
competitive salary and benefits, employee discounts after 3 months, etc.
Job Summary
They operate a cash register in a dynamic and courteous manner. By being the first and last contact with the customer, the cashier must always safeguard and promote the company’s image through their professionalism and the quality of their customer service. They must also ensure compliance with standards and procedures related to occupational health and safety.
Main Responsibilities
Operate a cash register;
Welcome customers;
Follow up on online orders and special counters;
Perform various administrative tasks;
Ensure the cleanliness of the premises;
All other related tasks.
Required Skills and Qualifications Profile
Training/Experience/Certification
Have experience with a cash register (an asset);
Have retail experience (an asset)
Knowledge
Have ease in using a computer system;
Have a good command of the French language, both orally and in writing.
Required Skills and Aptitudes
Be a good communicator;
Have the ability to solve problems quickly;
Be dynamic;
Have team spirit and good interpersonal skills.
Working Conditions
Daytime, evening and weekend schedule;
Standing work environment.
For any additional questions, please contact us: dotation@patrickmorin.com
